                <i class="fa fa-spinner fa-spin js-icon-loading"></i>
            </td>
            <td class="gap-line">
                                                    ... lines 12 - 23
                            </td>
            </tr>

        </tbody>
    </table>
</div>
</p>
<p>This won't work yet, but what I I <em>want</em> to be able to say is <code>{{ genus.updatedAt }}</code>.
If this existed and returned a DateTime object, we could pipe it through the built-in
Twig <code>date</code> filter to format it:</p>
<p><div class="code-block-wrapper" data-code-block-guid="104d12c198">
    <div class="meta">
        <div class="actions">
            <span class="fa fa-clipboard js-activate-clipboard" data-toggle="tooltip" title="Copy Code" data-placement="top"></span>
        </div>
        <div class="info">
                        <span class="js-expand-all" data-range="1-23" data-toggle="tooltip" title="Show All Lines" data-placement="top">
                <i class="fa fa-expand js-icon-load-more"></i>
                <i class="fa fa-spinner fa-spin js-icon-loading"></i>
            </span>
            
            23 lines <span class="meta-divider"></span> <span title="app/Resources/views/genus/list.html.twig">app/Resources/views/genus/list.html.twig</span>
        </div>
    </div>
    <table class="hljs code-block-table">
        <tbody class="js-tr-container">
                <tr>
                    <td class="line-number line-number-expandable" data-range="1-11" data-last="0">
